track_notes: A route submitted to the SMP on behalf of Terry G0VWP.
track_title: A 48 minute climb to Black Mount

track_notes: Use track up beside quarried rockface then veer to the right up grass cleft at NT 07960 46496, it gets hard for a while then eases once you see the fence where you head right.

This route runs from Hillside Gardens bus stop in Dolphinton between Black Mount and White Hill and then up Black Mount proper.

Selected because of ease of bus access the challenge starts at the turn off up Black Mount proper. There is no particular path and ankle deep heather all the way. Also note the very steep section in the middle. Its a reasonably short walk, but it is *very* steep.

The walk down is less physically demanding but the steep section still needs to be walked with care.

There is a fence at the turn off that will guide you directly to the summit.

Activation report here: https://reflector.sota.org.uk/t/gm-ss-158-black-mount-activation/32021/2
track_title: Hillside Gardens Bus Stop to Black Mount
